  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Relief Support to River Eroded People of Naria, Shariatpur (HI)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Reduce negative coping mechanism of the affected people and ensure food security
- Reduces health hazards and chance of disease outbreak
- Provide emergency shelter and protect from further harm
- Community take preventive action against diseases
- Communities will be aware about the response and the complain response mechanism</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The river erosion has taken a devastating turn in Shariatpur at Naria Upazila. Total casualty (dead/missing) is 35 people since last two years. According to government, 4200 families have been severely affected by the erosion in Naria while the local people and media say that a total of 5086 families have been affected (displaced) since last two months due to the erosion in Naria. About 27000 individuals of the affected families are suffering too much due to losing everything they had. More 8000 families are still at greater risk and vulnerable to the erosion.

4600 HHs will receive Multipurpose cash grants and have access to food, shelter and other basic lifesaving services 
4600 HHS have access to improved personal 
750 HHs have access to improved shelter
4600 affected persons in target villages benefit from improved hygiene &amp; sanitation
15000 affected people will have regular access in the information and complain response mechanism</narrative>
  </description>
